    "We note here that numerical characterization of this continuous transition, at the end of first-order transition line, is difficult within our numerical accuracy as nearby states have large correlation lengths.Effective field theory.-Various aspects of the phase diagram can be understood using an effective field theoretic analysis by mapping onto a parent Gaussian field theory [8,15] in presence of instabilities, described by the Euclidean action:S ≈ K 2π d 2 x (∇ϑ) 2 -h d 2 x cos(ϕ) -γ d 2 x cos (qϑ) -γ ′ d 2 x cos (2qϑ) +...,(4)where ϑ and ϕ are dual variables.",
    "We assume that all coupling constants, h, γ, γ ′,..., are small, and γ ′ > 0.The phase diagram of Eq.",
    "( 4), schematically shown in Fig. 3, can be determined by identifying the most relevant operator (in the RG sense) that would dominate long-distance physics [93].",
    "This, in turn, is determined by tracking the scaling dimensions of the various primary operators, which can be expressed in terms of the Luttinger parameter K as[cos ϕ] = K, [cos(qϑ)] = q 2 /(4K)and [cos(2qϑ)] = q 2 /K.",
    "For q > 4, a critical phase is obtained for 2 ≤ K ≤ q 2 /8 where no operator is relevant."
